'''Abbas Jirari''' ({{Lang-ar|عباس الجراري}} born 15 February 1937 in [[Rabat]]), also known as ''Abbas al-Jarari'', ''Abbas al-Jirari'' or ''Abbès Jirari'', is a Moroccan intellectual and advisor to King [[Mohammed VI of Morocco]].
==Biography== Jirari studied Arabic language and literature at the [[University of Cairo]] in [[Egypt]] and worked in the Moroccan ministry of foreign affairs in the 1960s. He is currently a professor at the Faculty of Arts and Humanities in Rabat.<ref>[http://uemnet.free.fr/guide/jim/jim06.htm uemnet.free.fr: عباس الجراري]</ref>
He was one of the 138 signatories of the open letter for Christian-Muslim dialogue [[A Common Word Between Us and You]].<ref>[http://www.acommonword.com/lib/downloads/gemeinsames_wort.pdf acommonword.com: A Common Word Between Us and You (summarized short form)] (PDF; 186&nbsp;kB)</ref>
He is married and the father of three children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diwanalarab.com/spip.php?article7862|title=عبـاس الجراري - ديوان العرب|website=www.diwanalarab.com|language=ar|access-date=2018-02-24}}</ref>
