{{refimprove|date=August 2016}}
'''Luis Garza Medina''' is a [[Roman Catholic]] priest of the [[Legion of Christ]] who previously served as its [[Vicar general|Vicar General]] and Territorial Director of North America. Garza is accused of sexually abusing a teenage boy in the early 1990s.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.courant.com/news/connecticut/hc-legionaries-sexual-assult-lawsuit-20161029-story.html/|title= New Sexual Abuse Lawsuit Filed Against Legionaries Of Christ|date= 28 October 2016|publisher= [[The Hartford Courant]] |accessdate= 7 November 2016}}</ref>

==Biography==
Garza was born and raised in [[Monterrey]], Mexico.  He has a bachelor's degree in industrial engineering from [[Stanford University]].  He entered the Legion of Christ in 1978. 

Garza became Vicar General of the Legion from 1992. In that office Garza is said to lead efforts to investigate charges of sexual misconduct brought against Legion founder [[Marcial Maciel]] although he had known about the abuses for years and chose to cover them up.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/former_legionaries_fr._garza_is_part_of_the_solution_not_the_problem/|title= Former Legionaries: Fr. Garza is part of the solution, not the problem|date= 31 March 2010|work= |publisher= [[Catholic News Agency]] |accessdate=20 April 2013}}</ref>

Garza resigned from the post of Vicar General in 2011 and was appointed Territorial Director for the United States and Canada.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/father-luis-garza-steps-down-at-vicar-general-of-legion-of-christ/
|title=Father Luis Garza steps down as Vicar General of Legion of Christ
|date=July 15, 2011
|accessdate=August 29, 2016
|author=David Kerr

}}</ref> 

His older brother [[Dionisio Garza Medina]] is  the CEO of Tenedora Topaz.  His younger sister [[Roberta Garza Medina]] is the editor of ''[[Milenio]]'' magazine in Mexico City.{{citation needed|date=September 2012}}

Garza today is believed to be living in the Philippines.

