'''Mohsin Changazi''', ({{lang-haz| محسن چنگیزی }}) (born September 3, 1979), is a Pakistani Urdu poet of [[Hazara people|Hazara]] descent.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hazara.net/news/mohsin/mohsin.html | title=Mohsin Changezi | publisher=Hazara | accessdate=August 17, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1008877/where-did-mohsin-changezi-go/|title=Where did Mohsin Changezi go? - The Express Tribune|date=12 December 2015|publisher=}}</ref> He has participated several poetry gatherings in Karachi, Lahore and Islamabad. He has also received awards including the [[Tamgha-e-Imtiaz]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.urdulife.com/mushaira/mehfil/mushaira.cgi?mnc_g1 | title=Mehfil Mushaira | publisher=UrduLife | accessdate=August 17, 2011}}</ref>
